---
import ExhibitionLayout from '../layouts/ExhibitionLayout.astro';
import ExhibitionMasthead from '../components/ExhibitionMasthead.astro';

// ABOUT US · letters A, B, O, U, T, U, S. Photo cutouts in B and O.
// Photos: use team headshots for the cutouts.
---
<ExhibitionLayout
  title="WHO WE ARE · The Keepers · SF Times"
  description="What the keepers is, who runs it, how it stays free."
  active="about"
>
  <ExhibitionMasthead
    slot="masthead"
    title="WHO WE ARE"
    subscript="SF TIMES"
    cutouts={[]}
  />

  <article class="ex-prose">
    <p class="ex-prose__eyebrow">MANAGING THE KEEPERS · A SATURDAY PUBLICATION</p>
    <h1 class="ex-prose__title">ONE KEEPER<br>EVERY SATURDAY.</h1>
    <p>
      The keepers is a weekly San Francisco profile publication. One issue every saturday morning. The subject is always a person holding something the city would lose without them. A recipe. A routine. A room. A record. A refusal. We name them. We photograph them. We let them speak.
    </p>
    <p>
      Reader-funded. No parent company. No paywall. No AI bylines. No banner ads. No tracking pixels. The five rules are real and stamped at the bottom of every issue.
    </p>

    <h2>WHAT WE PUBLISH</h2>
    <p>One profile a week, every saturday morning. Quarterly best of guides written by named editors. Reader-submitted hidden spots, vetted by the editor before they appear. Five personality quizzes that each end in a reading list. That's the whole publication.</p>

    <h2>HOW WE STAY FREE</h2>
    <p>Readers fund the reporting. We don't run banner ads. We don't sell your data. We don't have a paywall. Seventy-five percent of every donated dollar pays student journalists and editors. Twenty-five percent goes to local bay area charities, named on the support page, audited annually.</p>

    <h2>FIVE PRINCIPLES</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Named bylines, always.</strong> Every word on this site is written by a named human. No AI bylines, no syndicated filler, no aggregated reposts.</li>
      <li><strong>One thing per page.</strong> The homepage curates. The article reads. The best of guides. We don't cross-breed.</li>
      <li><strong>Specificity over abstraction.</strong> Real names, real prices, real dates. The shop owner is a person, not a stand-in for "small business."</li>
      <li><strong>Editorial firewall.</strong> Sponsored entries are labeled. The list still has to meet the editorial bar. Sponsors do not pick stories.</li>
      <li><strong>Protect the small.</strong> If a place can't handle traffic, we describe it without naming it. Hidden spots are the proof.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>WHO RUNS IT</h2>
    <p>Eric, founder and editor. Plus Nicholas and Daisy on the bylines, Kiwi on the photography. <a href="/team">Read the team page</a> for bios.</p>

    <h2>WHERE THE MONEY GOES</h2>
    <p>Full revenue breakdown lives on the <a href="/support">support page</a>. Editorial standards on the <a href="/standards">standards page</a>. Public corrections log on the <a href="/corrections">corrections page</a>. If we get something wrong we say so.</p>
  </article>

  <!-- FOUNDING SUPPORTERS WALL · social proof + slot scarcity -->
  <a href="#founders" class="ex-colmark__link">
    <section class="ex-colmark" id="founders">
      <h2 class="ex-colmark__text">FOUNDING SUPPORTERS</h2>
    </section>
  </a>

  <section class="supporters">
    <article class="ex-prose">
      <p class="ex-prose__eyebrow">NAMED · ALPHABETIZED · PERMANENT</p>
      <p>The keepers is reader-funded. Founding supporters are the first hundred who put their name behind the publication in its first year. Their names live here, in perpetuity, in alphabetical order. No tiers, no asterisks, no preferred logos. One line each.</p>
    </article>

    <ul class="supporters__list">
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">FIRST SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">SECOND SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">THIRD SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">FOURTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">FIFTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">SIXTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">SEVENTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">EIGHTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">NINTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">TENTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">ELEVENTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
      <li class="supporters__item supporters__item--open">TWELFTH SUPPORTER · YOUR NAME HERE</li>
    </ul>

    <article class="ex-prose">
      <p class="supporters__foot">Twelve founding spots reserved. The first hundred names anywhere on this page get permanent placement and locked 2026 pricing on any future renewal. After the first hundred, supporters appear on a dated yearly section. After ten years, every paying supporter is here. <a href="/support">Become a supporter →</a></p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <!-- Section divider wordmark before the team callout -->
  <a href="/team" class="ex-colmark__link">
    <section class="ex-colmark">
      <h2 class="ex-colmark__text">MEET THE TEAM</h2>
    </section>
  </a>

  <style>
    .supporters { padding: 0 12px 48px; max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .supporters__list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 32px 0;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 0 32px;
      border-block: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    @media (max-width: 720px) { .supporters__list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    .supporters__item {
      font-family: var(--display);
      font-size: clamp(15px, 1.6vw, 18px);
      letter-spacing: -0.005em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 14px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .supporters__item:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: 0; }
    .supporters__item--open { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }
    .supporters__foot { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 64ch; }
    .supporters__foot a { color: var(--ink); border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor; padding-bottom: 1px; font-weight: 600; }
  </style>
</ExhibitionLayout>
